{{Refimprove|date=October 2009}} {{Hungarianmusic}} The '''Hungarian Recording Industry Association''' (Hungarian: '''''Magyar Hanglemezkiadók Szövetsége''''', more commonly abbreviated to '''MAHASZ''' or '''Mahasz''') is the Hungarian [[music industry]] association, founded in 1992. MAHASZ issues the [[Hungarian Music Awards]] and maintains the [[music chart]]s for [[Hungary]].
==Certification levels== Certifications have existed in Hungary since the mid-1970s. During that period, albums had to sell 50,000 units to qualify for Gold status.<ref name="Gold awards 1974">{{cite journal|title=Billboard Vol. 86, No. 52|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hAkEAAAAMBAJ&q=%22hungary%22+%22no+Silver+disk+for+singles%22 |publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|page=40|date=1974-12-26|accessdate=2013-04-29}}</ref> Singles were required to sell 100,000 units to reach Gold level in the mid-1970s.<ref name="Gold awards 1974"/>
